I fucking love horse plinko. Like, first, the words "horse" and "plinko" don't even belong in the same sentence. They shouldn't be in the same paragraph and yet here they are next to each other. God never wanted those words next to each other. And then, it's so fucking simple in it's beauty. It's literally just horse plinko. It's plinko but with a ragdoll horse. It gives you everything, no questions asked. Even god couldn't put something lie that together. The sheer absurdity that two words and an animation with two assets - cylinders and a ragdoll horse is just so expertly crafted. The flames, of course, are just icing on the horse plinko cake.

Tfw you see a post talking about blorbo from your shows and its like the worst take ever.
They've misinterpreted this character completely and ignored justifications for characters being this way. The projection is like off the charts.
You're halfway through, and you're already fuming. You've got an essay length response halfway written in your head.
And that's when you realize, this is not actually in fact, blorbo from your shows. 
It is just some character from a show you've never watched that has the same name, and just enough similar trauma/problems/coping mechanisms to be mistaken for blorbo from your shows, who op could very well be right about, but you have no idea bc you've never seen the show. 
And so you quietly, mentally crumple up that essay you conjured up and try to go back to scrolling.

body: i think the reason the Horse Plinko meme does so well is because the best tumblr memes are versatile. lots of memes are only text based, or are just kind of one joke or picture over and over again. but something like this can be gifs, text posts, art, deep fried memes, there's a lot of transformative power because the joke is based on a concept, not a single line or image. and especially on tumblr, it gives it the opportunity to be done a lot, but in enough different ways that it doesn't immediately feel stale. i love Horse Plinko

body:
New test for media (I'm using Star Wars as an example but it really does work with everything) the Glup Shitto Test:
If a returning ("fan-favorite") character can be replaced by a generic one-off character named, say, Glup Shitto, and the characterization and plot wouldn't need to change to accommodate, the episode has failed the Glup Shitto Test.
This means that rather than doing the work to write for the character's unique voice and take into account the choices the character would make, the writers just chose to use said character as a callback or fan service.
This functions similarly to the Sexy Lamp test, in that it tests the writers' ability to provide unique and consistent characterization for everyone in the story. I'm using Star Wars as an example here because so much of their writing relies upon the whole "Look Who This Is!" gimmick, but it can absolutely apply elsewhere, whenever a piece of media brings back a fan-favorite character and it feels disappointing or inauthentic (Marvel and DC both come to mind). If Glup Shitto the Goofy Internet Meme just slots right in, there's work to be done.

 SCP-16195
Object Class:
 Safe
Special Containment Procedures:
 SCP-16195-1 is to be held in a standard humanoid containment cell along with SCP-16195. SCP-16195-1 must always have physical access to SCP-16195. Further testing is currently prohibited.
Description:
 SCP-16195 is a modified version of the home video game console developed by 
Sony Interactive Entertainment typically referred to as the 
PlayStation 5
. The person currently in legal possession of SCP-16195 is referred to as SCP-16195-1.
SCP-16195 is able to influence the thoughts and behavior of SCP-16195-1 in various ways, usually to prevent SCP-16195-1 from giving it away or to prevent itself from being destroyed. Separating SCP-16195 from SCP-16195-1 has only been successfully performed once, leading to [DATA EXPUNGED] and ownership of the item being transferred to the current SCP-16195-1.
Addendum 16195.1:
 Experiment log
SCP-16195-1 is prompted to choose between SCP-16195

and his girlfriend. He is then asked to write down what he is hearing in his mind.

body:
In the Hebrew Bible there are some words about which we don't know what they mean. And I don't mean, like, interpretation of the passages, I mean literally individual words that are only attested in this bit of the Bible. Obviously, we get the rough meaning from context and centuries of Rabbinical debates, because Rabbinical debates are dope, but this can only get us so far. In the Book of Jonah, for example, there is a leafy plant that has been translated as everything from grapes to cucumber.

body: The "it's me boy I'm the PS5" thing feels like a video game. Bad ending: girl smashes your console and leaves you. Normal endings: you give up gaming to keep your abusive gf or give up your gf and continue unhealthy gaming habits. "Good" ending: the player character is an even worse person than the girlfriend and somehow manipulates her into staying as the player character continues to destroy their life with too much console time. True ending: the player character breaks up with their abusive gf and finally starts putting in the effort to stop living life vicariously through video games; they'll still play but they won't stay up until the wee hours of the morning grinding games. Free will, it turns out, is not an illusion.

body:
If I had the energy to complete such a task I would make a long taped together scroll of paper, like a mockery of this site’s format, and make it into a long bullshit philosophical rant about the state of reality and Plinko the horse.
rough idea as to what would show up:
- plastic horse rolling down the strip of paper as it is coiled
- the illusion of choice and free will
- the inevitability of Plinko destroying the universe in a useless attempt to escape the fire, and the horse trainer’s equally useless attempt to stop Plinko
- a small reference to “rejected from the family learning channel”
- how the everything is not just one big game of plinko and that the majority of life does not fit cleanly into two boxes, or left and right when falling down
- the paper catching fire at the end consuming horse and all
- but then again can we really consider one fire different from another when it still leads to the same conclusion
- how overwhelming it can be to not be able to fully comprehend the situation that is being the horse trainer
-if the horse is unstoppable what happens if we drop it from a train running down the tracks at the same speed as it and the horse is coated in glue
- you think you might be the conductor of this train or are you actually the horse in this scenario it is hard to tell at the speed this is going
- you are horse trainer back at the beginning again but the act of trying to prevent this path is what created the chain in the first place
- the last thing seen on paper before the flames have finished is an incomplete answer or maybe a statement of “you are ”
- it is pretty much a video representing the slide into a panic attack caused by existential crisis being helplessly dragged along a train of thought by one increasingly complicated horse joke
- remember to drink some water message to cap it all off

Take me down to the eeby deeby
Where the deeb is eeb
And the eebs are deeby

Oh boy are English assignments fun. Had to do a free verse poem about any topic and I spat this out in one afternoon:
Blorbo from my Shows
, by the-razzdazzler
Blorbo from my shows
Blorbo from my games
Blorbo from my books
And Blorbo from my brain
Colors, shapes, and lines
All of them combined
Into a life, into a soul
Existing to assume the role
Of Blorbo from my shows
Blorbo doesn’t ask for much
He’s mostly just around
Although he can’t be seen or touched
One’s love for him abounds
Blorbo’s very patient
And doesn’t mind at all
If you obsess a little much
Or an amount that’s small
Blorbo is like a tinted mirror
He is what I would be
If I were perfect, through and though
If confidence suited me
While nobody is flawless
Blorbo breaks that rule
Even his imperfections
Make him a brighter jewel
Blorbo lives in a far-off land
It’s known as Eeby Deeby
The only way to reach him
Is through my daydreaming
Some told me there was a way
A way to finally meet him
If I focused hard enough
And did some meditations
My mind would leave my body
And I’d somehow hop dimensions
I never could find Blorbo
He stayed within his shows
I’ll never get to tell him
Blorbo will never know
That he’s become my muse
My reason to create
But our paths will never cross
It was never my fate
I think of Blorbo often
It helps me to escape
My life becomes more bearable
If he is in my day
Many say it’s wrong
Some call it demented
To always be in fantasy
To live with things invented
But who would want to lock this up?
Would want life grey and paler?
I’ve pondered this quite often
And the answer would be:
Jailers

body:
Don't you just love when a show doesn't release all episodes of a new season at the same time? It makes each episode so much more special when you have to wait for the next one. You go "oh! today is sunday. that's the day i set aside to keep up with my blorbos. these blorbos are special because they only come around once a week." 
And the suspense! Yes! Keep me on my toes. Show me this guy's twin brother waking up for a coma, then make me wait 7 days before showing me his next move. I don't have the self-restraint to not binge watch all 14 episodes in two days, but I also don't have the attention span for doing so.
The most memorable shows are not the ones that release everything at the same time. It's the ones that let the events of one episode sink in before showing you the next.

body:
It’s a beautiful shining day. The sky’s a clear, crisp blue with not a cloud in sight, the sun shimmering in the sky. A sweet gentle breeze flows through the wind. It’s a perfect day, the best kind for a wedding.
You bore into beautiful eyes, glistening with unfiltered love and adoration; bearing right down into the depths of your soul. They like what they see. Cheeks dusted lightly with glitter? No, they just shine with joy and passion, perched up to hold a smile. All for you.
Words spoken by an older person. A priest perhaps? It doesn’t matter. What does is this moment, shared by two soon to be one, united for generations to see. At least, that’s what you hope. Seems like they share the same sentiment. “…speak now or forever hold your peace.”
“I object”
A booming voice echos through the venue. Shock and bafflement quickly shoot through your veins. A small gasp comes from your beloved, as they whip their head to the voice, only to cover their mouth in aghast. You slowly turn to view the speaker, the only one who dared to object your union.
It’s the PS5.

You were in the Mondstadt library reading a book you borrowed from Lisa, literally falling asleep when venti burst thought door. Venti knew you liked to take a break in the library, but it wasn't often you fell asleep here. After speed walking through many isles of books he finally found you, on the upper level of the library, eyes slowly closing while your head falls against the wall behind you. After finding you he ran up the stairs and (once again) speed walked to you.
"Windblume! Oh, windblume?"
He slowly approached your half asleep body, you noticed his appearance after 2 steps towards you.
"Oh, hello venti"
You say with a yawn, lifting your head to look at him. He tackles you with a hug before sitting down in front of you.
"What are you doing here? Your usually not the type to go to a library"
Your confused expression made venti laugh.
"Well, a bard has to get their storys somewhere, right?"
He switch positions so his head was in your lap, moving the book you had in your hands to your side.
"But today I came for you"
The former archon spoke before he took your hand and kissed it. You start to blush while he chuckles and  kisses your hand again. After the moment past, you started to yawn, feeling as if your about to fall into a dream.
"You can rest windblume, I promise I'll look out for you"
venti said as he held both of your hands. You smile  at your boyfriend as he laid in your lap, whispering to you how he will make sure you have nothing but sweet dreams as you close your eyes. After a while, he started to grow tired, and soon closed his eyes to sleep and see the dream with you.

So when I tell you that the American School System is fucked. Believe me.

there’s a failure in mainstream media, caused by the treacherous drive of marketability, the cursed attempt to make characters that Everyone can Relate to, to make actually relatable, personable characters. witty one liners do not a human make. however, audiences crave connection; our monkey brains desire patterns and identification in the content we consume. hence the “blorbo from my shows” phenomenon, where any character, no matter how minor (background figure in grimdark drama, professional cipher in a crime of the week from decades ago, someone who inhabits the cut scenes of a rhythm game), can be infused with all the audience members personal traits, preferences, diagnoses etc. blorbo in the show (
blorbo a
, if you will) should ideally be someone whom the author/s will not expand on, allowing the audience to fill in the narrative detail as best suits their own interpretation of blorbo (
blorbo petit a
). we apophenically identify connection between blorbo and ourselves as well as pop songs, poems, classical art, high fashion and so on, putting significantly more thought and consideration into the character than the author/s did. in this essay, i will

i think i found the formula to make tumblr words!
- stress always lands on the first syllable
- ends in o, y, or an stop consonant (-p, -t, -k)
- use voiced plosives (g, d, b), unvoiced fricatives (s, f, h), and approximants (y, w, l, r)
- almost always start with a plosive+approximant combo (bl, gr, dw) or a fricative+plosive combo (sc, sht)

My hundred closest friends and I go quiet as he walks into the room. Tall, dark, handsome. His dress is inappropriate for such an event, but the upper-class look in his eye puts all the new money couture down for a quiet death. My closest of the close, Clara, leans sideways toward me, still facing the delicate centerpiece and whispers, "how could you let him come back?" 
I don't quite have an answer for her. I don't yet have an answer for myself. How could I? Perhaps the issue isn't that I don't have an answer, but far too many. I invited him because he's interesting. Because his presence might get this affair published. Because I love him, still. Because I once loved him more. 
The hens around the table start clucking out a questionnaire like I'm a typewriter for them to collect their supposed 'thoughts."
"Who is he wearing?"
"Who is he with?"
"When did he come back to town?"
Finally, my dear, sweet cousin, Katie speaks. She's new to the life of a socialite, though it is her birth rite. "What's his name?"
I was so lost in my own unyielding thoughts, that I hadn't noticed he had snuck up on me. From behind, I heard a diaphanous voice begin, one so once familiar, now shocking.
"Plinko. Horse Plinko."

Tumblr as an academic source
So I previously said I’m in a class on American Folklore. Our next written assignment is a paper on a meme that helped us at any point in the pandemic and I’m doing mine on horse plinko!
It may have only been around for a short time, but damn was it entertaining in a time where my girlfriend was in quarantine with the plague. I’m currently struggling with which iteration to use. 
Should I just use the original?
In any case, I’m so fucking hype for this chaotic shit.

I love the 
blorbo/scrunglo
 chat on this website so much. It’s just so cool to me that the characters we’ve made entire worlds out of and that are our happy places that genuinely help us to get through the day sometimes are literally nothing more than pixels on a screen to others. And that equally, characters that just look like dudes to me are somebody else’s favourite thing in the whole world.
It’s like that feeling when you look at a stranger and are struck by the fact that they have entire lives full of people and memories that you know nothing of, and for a moment you feel the full weight of how rich and complex the world really is. 
We all have our own blorbos and I think that’s beautiful.

body: i think it's unfair to water down "blorbo" to simply mean favorite character. i think the two intersect so it works as a simplified definition but i feel as though blorbo has much greater nuance. a blorbo resides in your mind. you do not necessarily wish exclusively fond things upon your blorbo but rather you want to witness your blorbo experience a wide array of emotion just to continue experiencing their character. i think a favorite character is one that you enjoyed most out of the experience of the media. you give your heart to a favorite character but a blorbo finds yours and holds it hostage until you face the inevitable clutches of blorbofied stockholm syndrome.

"It had come to his knowledge, he said, that a foolish and wicked rumour had been circulated at the time of Boxer's removal. Some of the animals had noticed that the van which took Boxer away was marked "Horse Plinko" and had actually jumped to the conclusion that Boxer was being sent to the plinko.
It was almost unbelievable, said Squealer, that any animal could be so stupid. Surely, he cried indignantly, whisking his tail and skipping from side to side, surely they knew their beloved Leader, Comrade Napoleon, better than that? But the explanation was really very simple. The van had previously been the property of the plinko, and had been bought by the veterinary surgeon, who had not yet painted the old name out.
That was how the mistake had arisen."
-Animal Farm, Chapter 9 (George Orwell)

body:
Writing Challenge: ride your Horse Plinko towards Eeby Deeby
Alright, Writeblr, I have got a challenge for you. Have you noticed the plethora of strange, made up tags that are floating around Tumblr lately? You know, Horse Plinko, Eeby Deeby, Blorko and so on?
Well, what if I challenge you to take all these names and turn them into OCs? If you are writing a story, try to imagine them as characters within that story. Otherwise, let your imagination roam free. Who knows: maybe, this could give you a whole cast of characters for a new project.
By the way, here is the list of names to use.
Horse Plinko
Eeby Deeby
Blorko
Blorbo
Cousin Throckmorton
Beb
Scrunkly
Scrunco
The Zozz
Scrimblo Bimblo
Wakazonga
I will go first, to show you what I mean with this.
A brief guide for wanderers who want to reach Eeby Deeby
So, imagine for a moment that you are ready for a quest. You have everything prepared: your weaponry, your everyday objects, your clothing and such. However, you don’t seem to have any idea about the area you need to reach.
What’s an Eeby Deeby, and why can you only reach it by riding a Horse Plinko? Well, no need to worry. I am here to brief you about what you might encounter in your journey. So, sit back, and let me explain. Things could get real confusing real quickly if you don’t follow me.
Horse Plinko: what’s a Knight without their noble steed by their side? This horse, however, is no ordinary horse, and you can see from the way it gallops around. If you ever have to ride on it, you would feel like you are just constantly bouncing from one place to another, without any safety measure. In fact, it is suggested to either wear your full plated armour or to have a protection spell with you. Sure, you may end up smashing around every tree in the forest, but the fun will make up for it. Of course, make sure you don’t get near fireplaces: for some reason, a Horse Plinko seems attracted to those.
Eeby Deeby: fun fact, Eeby Deeby is both a place 
and 
a species of beings! To reach Eeby Deeby, you need to find special portals, the types that can only be accessed by carving runes on it, obviously spelling 
Eeby Deeby
. Once you do so, you will be greeted by an Eeby Deeby, which is specifically there to send you to their namesake homeland. Because nobody 
goes
to Eeby Deeby, you are 
sent
 to Eeby Deeby. Of course, what’s in there depends on your wishes and your desires. For some, that could be a beautiful nightmare. For others, a confusing dreamland. So, are you ready to hop on your Horse Plinko and reach the portal to Eeby Deeby? No worries, for you won’t be alone in this.
Blorko: picture this. You just rode on your Horse Plinko on your way to the Eeby Deeby portals, right? As such, you have spent minutes and minutes just there, on a landscape that seems to never end. Then, all of a sudden, you notice someone walking from behind the trees. Don’t worry, it is not a trap. In fact, there they are, walking towards you, and announcing themselves. “It’s me, Blorko!” is something you are destined to hear when you walk there.
Blorbo: in that area, there are some actors which seem to be everywhere. You can’t watch a single play or walk nearby a theatre without seeing one of them. An actor from that company is called Blorbo, and the company’s name is “Blorbos from your shows”, and they enjoy spreading their acting abilities, especially because, usually, a Blorbo is the most charismatic and appreciated actor in any play. Sure, you may be wondering: what happens when more Blorbos act together? Joy, pure joy. Also, don’t confuse them with Blorko, although some say Blorko likes to go to Eeby Deeby with a Blorbo.
Cousin Throckmorton: who’s Cousin Throckmorton, you ask? Well, he’s the definition of “extreme awesomeness” around here. He doesn’t just run to a place, but he has to back-flip while holding a flaming bagpipe and riding one Horse Plinko per limb. Everybody calls him “Cousin Throckmorton”, not because he is related to everyone here, but because everyone wishes they could brag about him being their cousin. Of course, this results in the awkwardly funny experience of trying to figure out who is actually related to him.
Beb: Beb is strange, because you don’t know what to expect from her when you have a conversation. One minute, she’s there discussing about how magnificent is the sky, or how profound the words of a poet are, and then, the next minute, she just stands there, replying “beb” to everything. Also, you don’t seem to see her as often as, say, Blorko and Cousin Throckmorton, so wanderers who randomly encounter someone saying “beb” feel confused.
Scrunkly: a Scrunkly is a typical animal of the area. Aesthetically, it resembles an earless fox, and tends to look at people straight in the eyes. Not as a sign of intimidation, but because they are adorably curious. Everyone here likes to have a Scrunkly as a pet.
Scrunco: someone who enjoys a Scrunkly a little too much is called a Scrunco. They always talk in “pet language”, as if they are just cuddling their Scrunkly. They are not weird or dangerous. Just, don’t feel awkward if they start acting like you’re a really cute pet.
The Zozz: if Beb is someone you rarely see, the Zozz is even rarer. They say they only reached the place at the beginning of this year, replacing an inhabitant named Zozi, of whom they’re apparently the heir. No one is sure about what they do, because they pop up at very random places.
Scrimblo Bimblo: unlike Beb and the Zozz, Scrimblo Bimblo’s obscureness seems a bit intentional. They are apparently a hero from a faraway land that only a handful of people have even heard about, and they would keep mentioning their quests as if they are the greatest hero who has ever graced this realm, and as such their exclusion in any discussion about heroic people should be seen as a disgrace. To be fair, Scrimblo Bimblo seems like a nice, down to earth person, so people are merely annoyed by how much those around them would talk non-stop about them.
Wakazonga: apparently, it is a benevolent monster who uses its name as a powerful attack. Whenever they shout “wakazonga!”, in fact, a surge of energy appears, which can be used for a lot of things, to the point where the area treats Wakazonga as a source of power. Also, it is this monster which can help you activate the portal to Eeby Deeby, so you might want to find it. Don’t worry, you will be fine.
So, are you ready for your trip? I hope you can enjoy it as much as everyone else is.
THE END
Alright, Writeblr, I challenge you to do the same, now. Let’s have some fun together!

body:
(CW death, afterlife)
After a long and happy life, you start to feel yourself fade away... but you don't. You hear a raging fire, and look below you to see countless pegs above a field of flames. You're falling, hitting each peg one by one, but you never seem to get any closer to the flames. You try to stop yourself from falling by hanging onto one of the pegs, but it doesn't work, your spine has already been decimated by the drops. As you ragdoll down what appears to be an infernal game of plinko, you happen to glance upon your own arms for a mere fraction of a second, and see that you have hooves, and have become a horse. As your equine form continues to plummet, you wonder what you could've possibly done to deserve this afterlife. Is this hell? It doesn't really matter anymore however. There is nothing more you can do but fall and fall forever in this eternal game of horse plinko.

Randomly thinking about Kate McKinnon and Leslie Jones, and their respective characters (Jillian Holtzmann, the Engineer & Patty Tolan, the Historian) in the "Ghostbusters: Answer the Call (2016)" film, and now I'm debating about having a solo film re-watch this Sunday, if I complete my chores/errands first perhaps.
The need for some leisurely levity is compelling, indeed.
*****
And on that random fandom thoughts, I have to laugh at myself a bit for realizing that I definitely 
do
 have quite predicable favorite character type(s) in media/books/films/etc., afterall.  Which are all fictional characters with some simultaneous combinations of othered/queer/gender-non-conformity/neurodivergent/underdog coding; strong, unabashed adokableness/nerdiness; wittiness; intellectual, ambivertedness/introvertedness, artistic skills/creativity skills/ingenuity/giftedness; perseverance/resiliency/grit/strength; protective & selfless/heroic natures; and a genuinely, authentically loving/kind/gentle core personality beneath a front of an armored guardedness/reservation/initial outward abrasiveness.  Or in contrast, if a villainous character-type, then often, pure confidence/prowess/competence/badassery; mad scientist/genius/intellect/cleverness; and a quality of being misconstrued/misunderstood but sympathetic badness/evil-doing/amorality (with a dash of the possibility for a redemption arc/anti-hero story arc narratively), I suppose.
Which, honestly, should be totally obvious to me upon any amount of self-reflective analysis because like some of these common traits in these fictional characters are some of the very same relatable facets of my own self and how I have come to subjectively/objectively understand what so has shaped/shapes me, at times.  An obvious sentiment also in and of itself for the myriad reasons folks are intended to relate to/resonnate with fictional characters.
Like going off on a nostalgia tangent, thinking about just a random assortment of favorite characters apropos of stream-of-consciousness and in no particular order or category and across multiple medias for various reasons:
[Semicolons (;) to indicate separate favorite characters from within the same media that stand on their own as being loved for their characterization, fictional role, and traits in the story/media (i.e., not in any relation to any sort of additional headcannon/fan shipping sense of attachment/affection towards such character(s))

Bojack Horseman is the Plinko horse
Bojack Horseman is the Plinko horse. 
In this essay, reason will be given to believe that Bojack Horseman (from the hit Netflix original, 'Bojack Horseman'), and the Plinko horse are metaphorically tied to one another.
At first glance, the characters Bojack Horseman and the Plinko horse are very different, their only similarity being that they are both horses. And yet, when one ponders more deeply into the true meaning of both media, implicit details can begin to tie the two together in very interesting and compelling ways.
In order to fully understand this connection, one must assume that the Plinko board represents Bojack's life and that the incinerator below is representative of his jail sentence. Bojack is constantly battered as he goes through his life and falls onto the pegs of hardship and happenings, each one only knocking him further down the board (his life). the y-axis on the board represents time progression whilst the x-axis represents his emotions. 
Each peg (life event) that he falls onto will knock him either right or left, thus changing him emotionally. And this happens while life still keeps moving onwards.
The Plinko horse (Bojack) never travels up the Plinko board, only down. (Time’s arrow neither stands still nor reverses, it merely marches onwards). 
The incinerator at the bottom of the Plinko board (his life) represents the ending of the show, where, his entire life and outlook are changed. When Bojack goes to jail, he finally gets consistency and stability in his life. He learns how to live well. his past life and the horse he once was is ‘incinerated’. And after the Plinko horse has been destroyed, nobody knows what happens next. Just like we, as a viewer, don’t know what the next chapter of Bojack’s life is.
Another important view to note is how the Plinko horse is viewed. Being a mere internet meme, it is not seen with levels of complexity and nuance that allow room for the emotional exploration of the Plinko horse's torment. This is similar to how those around Bojack view him. His struggles often aren't fully appreciated by others, merely used as a tool to further scorn or ridicule him. The Plinko horse and Bojack both travel down their lives being laughed at and not taken as seriously as they should, considering their levels of torment.
In conclusion, while explicitly, it can be hard to draw similarities between the two horses, when explored further, important and heavily metaphorical connections can be found that help to further understand both Plinko horse, and Bojack Horseman.

body:
People who are like me and don’t know what the new words like glup shittos, here you go:
Glup shittos
: 
 a fake name used online to refer to returning characters from the Star Wars extended universe in newer mainstream Star Wars media, which are known and praised by hardcore fans but unknown to the more general audience.
Blorbo
:
 (from my show) 
 is a slang term for a person's favorite fictional character and is used similarly to terms such as Glup Shitto and Scrimblo Bimblo. Though initially intended as a mocking way to describe Tumblr fandoms, it began seeing more use among fandoms as it became popularized in early 2022.
Blorko: 
On Dec 18 2021 Twitter user @mrbasil_pesto tweet “My favorite bit  of Marvel films is when you  sit through nine minutes of credits to watch a five second clip of some guy  stepping through a doorway and saying “It’s me, Blorko.”
Scrimblo Bimblo: 
fictional video game character used in a viral tweet to exaggeratedly describe how angry some Super Smash Bros. Ultimate players get when their favorite characters from nostalgic games aren't added to the game, particularly when JRPG characters are added in favor of them. The name is also used broadly to refer to frequently requested Smash characters, and as a sort of insult towards people who demand them.
Scrunkly: (Awww The Scrunkly, continued 🥰🥺🥺🥺🥺🥺🥺🥺🥺🥺🥺🥺 Double Tap Now if You'd Scrunkly the When😆) 
is a nonsense phrase and copypasta featured in a series of image macros, often attached to random images and images of animals that have an indefinable "scrunkly" quality to them. The first example of the meme features a low-res image of a fox and was posted to Instagram in May 2021.
Eeby Deeby
 
refers to an impersonation of robot speak and has since been used in a series of edited comics whose speech bubbles have been edited to have one character say "Your dick cold" and the other say "Eeby Deeby." Often, the two characters will be situated such that it can look like they're having sex. The trend started with an edit of a still from a Buck Rogers comic strip of the robot character Twiki before it was adapted to fit multiple images online.
Eeby Deeby elevator
 
meme on Feb. 1, from Tumblr user @theweirdwideweb, uploaded an image of an elevator with the caption, "Where the f*ck is this thing taking me?" The elevator floor on the screen isn't a number; instead it reads, “eeby deeby,” original the elevator had a UwU face 
Eeby Deeby elevator 2.0 
another way to say your going to hell, using in a joking manner
Horse Plinko 
refers to a viral animated GIF of a horse falling through a Plinko board as it bounces off pegs. Originating from a demonstration video for a computer science paper, 
Throckmorton
, 
also known as John Thomas sign, refers to when the penis points in the direction of unilateral disease, typically of the pelvis or hip. Throckmorton sign is a slang term used humorously by medical students 
Cousin Throckmorton
, 
aka Throcky, refers to a fictional character who appeared in a physics textbook word problem. In the problem, "Cousin Throckmorton" is a skateboarder, and the student is tasked with discovering the speed at which he descends a ramp and the force acting on him at the bottom of his descent. Once a Twitter user posted a screenshot of the question, it spread on social media, with people making jokes about Cousin Throckmorton, the skateboarder.

Hey old-timers, all this new-fangled lingo scrimbloing your brainbos? Enter I, your savior, with this helpful guide:
Blorbo (from my shows): A portmanteau of blue and orb with the -o tacked on to enhance friendliness. The phrase is the command “from my shows” addressed to the blue orb (blorbo). The orb will then show you visions of that which is from your shows.
Glup Shitto: A fictitious, profane sex act conceived in retaliation against the great ban of ‘18 that has resurfaced as some degenerates have tried performing it for real. E.g. “Hey bro, my parents aren’t home, want to netflix and glup shitto?” 
Scrunglo: An insult derived from the word scrungy (shabby/grungy/unkempt) used in fandom for those with bad taste, usually as it pertains to ships (their taste is scrungy and unrefined). E.g. “That Scrunglo is crazy about [whatever ship you happen to have a hate boner for].”
And finally the big trending man itself...
Eeby Deeby: Hell. In straightforward usage, you can be sent to Eeby Deeby (Superhell), but someone may also Eeby your Deeby (gay you, as Cas did in spn getting him sent to Superhell). Ebay Deebs may also refer to this Hellsite.
Hope this was unhelpful!

Hallowed Be Thy Name
He hovered amongst the stars, watching reality unfold before him. He studied many worlds, but could find no place where his inanimate nature would bring any substance. His curse, from the ancient time before time, was nonexistence. With this, he sustained a passion for reality.
He studied many worlds. For him, they all played out in the same ways for entirely different reasons. Even those reasons progressed for the exact same purpose. Yet, for him, nothing had ever happened. He tirelessly searched for the perfect place to relay his infinite silence.
Of all the worlds he studied, he only recognized the one in which he saw nothing at all. The world where names did not matter, had no meaning, and made no impact. In this world, he experienced the truest nature of connection.
He descended from the stars, eager to inhabit this one true sanctuary. When he emerged, he could only laugh at the realization that his name was Blorbo, and that he belonged to every story, every affinity, and every understanding.
He had emerged as a sentiment of substitution. A placeholder for every hero, fool, and villain. No single individual could claim to be him, but he could be anyone. Anyone that related to any scenario, situation, or belief carried him with them. You could be him. I could be him. No one could be him. He had achieved the greatest freedom of doing nothing, being nothing, yet belonging to anything. 
He still hovers amongst the stars, as every constellation in mythology is Blorbo from your shows.
What I can see as the result of Tumblr's current meme obsession is a future generation of horses who are all named Plinko

body:
I’m Fandom Old so here is my attempt at defining the new terms with The Old Language of Fandom. 
A 
Blorbo
 is your favorite character, a character you relate to, or a character you otherwise find compelling in a way that makes them occupy your brain, often even outside of a fandom context. If they’re meant to be relatable, they may be an 
Audience Surrogate
. If they fulfill some kind of wish fulfillment in you, they’re an 
Escapist Character
. And if you feel sorry for them/want to protect them/or enjoy when they are on the receiving end of angst or whump, they might also be a 
Woobie
. If they are a 
Woobie
, they are also probably 
Scrunkly
. 
Now if your character is 
Scrunkly
, they could also easily be a 
Woobie, Destroyer of Worlds 
if they are pushed too far and have a 
Face-Heel Turn
. If this is the case, they can easily become your 
Poor Little Meow Meow
. If they are a 
Poor Little Meow Meow
, they are almost certainly a 
Draco in Leather Pants
. I personally believe that it’s also possible to make a 
Butt-Monkey
 your 
Poor Little Meow Meow
, but that’s less common and 
YMMV
 on that. 
Now if your 
Blorbo
 or your 
Poor Little Meow Meow
 is a 
Scrimblo Bimblo
, they’re probably an 
Ensemble Dark Horse
. Whereas if they are a 
Glup Shitto
, they are more likely a 
Memetic Bystander
. 
Hope this helps! <3

Been thinking abt all the different Brands of favorite characters I have and how complicated it can be trying to answer the simple question of "oh, who's your favorite one?" when asked, so I made a list. Feel free to fill this out and share with folks: 
Blorbo: Fave you base your online identity on, the one you instinctively think of when people in fandom spaces ask who your fave is. They're probably your discord icon.
Kinnie: Your kin, the one people say you're kin with or the one you feel the most similar to in your heart. Doesn't necessarily have to be your Blorbo, tho they can overlap. 
Meow meow: Your pathetic, evil little fave. You know he's trash but you still want to put him in your little basket and carry him around like a cool rock you found on a walk.
Skeeb deeby: The one who, anytime you see him in the background for a second, you gasp outloud bc!! It's him!! 
The Spouse(TM): You find them incredibly hot and wanna settle down with them. Genuine admiration and a level of attraction (sexual or otherwise).
Gremlin: Anytime they get up to their antics, you can't help but laugh, even if they're morally duplicitous or repugnant. Different vibe from Meow Meow.
It's Complicated(TM): Unless you have 10 minutes to explain the complexities of your feelings about this character and why you relate to them despite their general Reputation, then you don't bother mentioning theyre a favorite.
Gender Envy: You want to be them. You want what they have.

body:
I had this idea of a plinko horse comic that I only ended up doing basic lineart form that had this dialogue going on:
“Im so sick, so tired, so hurt. What have I done that deserves so much punishment. Why can’t I ever escape you no matter how much I try to
Oh little horse, do you really believe my embrace to be a punishment? Are my warm flames all that terrifying?
I’m sorry if that is so, for all I wish is for you is to be at peace. You fall, slide and bump perpetually. You know no rest, nor no smile. So I’m the break. I hug you tenderly and embrace you until we become one. I laugh and give you voice in a way no one peeking will ever understand. I hold your scared face and kiss it gently.
And then… we repeat.
If that’s the case, then why do i never remember it? Why do I try to run away?
You always remember. You’re just too tired to acknowledge the truth. 
Well, I am acknowledging it now! Why can’t I stay here, why can’t I be with you and finally be free.
Freedom is what keeps the cycle going. Kindness is just what brings you back to me.
- - -
And there will be days where you will live without a care in the world, surrounded by grass and sun. And there will be days where I am nowhere near your sight, as you plunk down between concrete and tears. And yet… we will always come back to the same dance, and I will be here for when you need me.”

A Horse Went Down a Plinko
A choose your own adventure fic.
You are Horse.
Read it on Ao3 here: 
https://archiveofourown.org/works/36348358
(Warning for animal death right off the bat)
The shot to the head had been sloppy.
A shot made for efficiency, quickness, unconcerned with the humaneness of the death.
And Horse was 
dying
.
The hole in their head pulsed as blood and brain matter oozed out of it but the pain was slowly, slowly, fading. Their limbs grew stiff with their efforts to get in one last kick. But they simply spasmed, uncontrollably.
Horse wasn’t sure if they wanted to die.
Horse didn’t have a choice.
Their vision went black. Their whole body tingled and it was cold….The sensation of falling came over them.
Horse was no longer laying in a puddle of their own blood; Horse was 
falling
.
Falling
.
Thud
.
Horse cried out. They’d landed? Something broke their fall.
Horse felt themself begin to fall again. Their body teetering over the edge of the something.
Thud
.
Fall.
Thud
.
Fall.
Thud
.
Their body limp, their fall was interrupted by a series of 
somethings
, only ever momentarily stopping their descent into wherever it was horses went when they died.
Horse was dead.
Thud
.
Fall.
Had Horse been good?
Thud
.
Fall.
Was this where horses went when they died? It didn’t hurt…But it wasn’t… nice…
THUD
.
And Horse didn’t fall.
Horse tried to open their eyes but found they weren’t closed. Horse couldn’t see.
But Horse could 
smell
; Horse smelled salt and breeze, and a bitter, earthy smell that they didn’t recognize.
The last thud had been different, hollow and metallic.
And horse was no longer falling…
 Horse was 
floating
? Gently bobbing up and down; the sound of water rushing in their ears.
“Hello, Horse.”
The voice was different than Horse had ever heard before. It wasn’t like the masters’ garbled nonsense.  Horse could understand it; but it wasn’t like another horse. Horse didn’t try to reply. Horses couldn’t speak but to other horses.
“You will have to speak, horse,” the voice echoed in their head, deep and powerful, not ominous or frightening, but not exactly comforting either… “You must speak, for you must answer.”
Horse didn’t respond.
“Do you consider yourself irredeemable?”
“Wh-What?” Horse tried their voice.
“Are you worthy of damnation?”
Reblog with "Yes." or "No." 
The option with the most answers decides the story <3.

One day they were talking about all the different scents they wanted to get and comparing prices/functionality and they said “sorry, you probably don’t know what I’m talking about.” And I said “Blorbo from Your Cleaning Products.” They cracked up, and have been referring to them exclusively as Blorbos ever since.
They’ll be cleaning and say “Do you know where my Blorbos are? No, the peony Blorbo?”
Or sentences that are almost incomprehensible like, “I can’t find my Blorbo or my Blorbo, have you seen them?”

Fear dripped down the males face in beads of sweat, breath heavy as he hid underneath the desk. He couldn't, no, 
wouldn't
 end up like this. He was one of the fastest runners in school, there was... there was no way it had caught up. A scythe pierced through the desk, nearly going right through the boys skull. Well that answers his question. He shoved the desk onto the creature, stumbling to stand and starting to run again. It can't take him, not today. Any day but today. He was supposed to go dancing with his mother tonight, in the skating arena. He has to be there for her. His thoughts were cut off, a second creature appearing in front of him and nearly taking his head off. He was trapped, between the monsters. This was it. The scythes struck, sending him into blackness.
Soon, though, the soft sound of 1980s music and bright white lights brought him back. An elevator. He was in an elevator, next to a large angel. "Wh... where are you taking me?"
"Why, son, this elevator is taking us straight to eeby deeby."

body:
I have to talk about some blorbos from my shows for a minute bc I rewatched love & anarchy/kärlek & anarki and I can't stop thinking about the PLANTS!!
Like, Sofie has her whole 'a girl who is a seed/rose/forest/etc' metaphor from her book, and max grows plants in his little apartment yeah? And when Sofie sees them she complements his plants :) and Max complements her story :) while most of the other ppl in each of their lives make fun of them for their hobbies
And the song Roses by Soleima, which plays twice in the series, just fits so perfectly!! It's about standing up to people who try to change you, very fitting for the relationship between Sofie and her husband:
"But are roses red and are violets blue?
So what the fuck did you think that you could do?
Change me, really?
Thank God bless you for the truth
Roses, red roses, now theyre just dead roses, baby"
The moment when Sofie finally snaps at her husband and decides she won't move to London? They're at the spa, in hot tub with rose petals floating all around them.
Also, roses symbolize love and romance, so dead roses = dead love, the end of a relationship
Like?? The whole series is about about growing and rebelling and shedding past versions of yourself. By the end of the season Sofie isn't the same person she was in her relationship with her husband. She's not a rose, she's a forest now! And despite how messy the whole situation is, and how absurd their methods are, Sofie and Max support each other in their growth as people!!

body:
On Bilingual Bonuses
"Blorbo from my shows" sounds like a typically secular, Tumblrite construct, but it happens to remind me of something my mother and grandmother used to employ in order to refer to their favourite audience hooks in the local sitcom dubs. 
"Les filles de mes programmes"
, or "The girls from my programs", where "program" refers to a TV show.
Think about it: you spend an afternoon hoovering in dubs for 
The Young and the Restless, Melrose Place, Beverley Hills 90210, Models Inc. 90210, Dynasty, Santa Barbara, 
with all of them using the same stylistic guide, all of them framing dialogues in the same way, all of them using similar dramatic stings to underline a reveal or a plot twist. How long is it before everything blends together and you start wondering if Stacey knows who RJ Ewing is and if Sarah is aware that Steve is banging her clone?
Mom and Grandma had their Blorbos when I was a kid, some of them sharing the same dub VA over several years apart. Add to that the fact that I was a barely-fluent French Canadian kid who only paid cursory attention to the whole thing, and the whole stretch between 3 and 6 PM seemed populated by a legion of Glup Shittos to me - one of which is wearing what I didn't know to be a ten-gallon hat at the time.
Seeing how often dramatic deaths shook things up, you can only assume that Eeby Deeby and Super Hell both fought for rights over 
Loving
's Stacey Forbes...

body: What if the real eeby deeby was tumblr all along

Immediately, the horse sprung into action. He moved with a preternatural speed and agility; a machine of oiled muscle, a brilliant quicksilver torrent, a cascade of light and flesh and sound, a god. A god.
Lips pulled back, mane whirling, eyes frothing, ears billowing, hooves pulverizing, legs pumping like the pistons in the engine of a hearse. One horsepower was more than enough to drive this h(ea/o)rse on his journey to the grave and back again. This was the n(e)igh-celestial body of an animal who would run into a burning plinko, not out of stupidity, but out of defiance, out of refusal to believe that the flames could so much as singe him.
This… was a horse. This was a fucking horse.

body:
A Poem For Blorbos
-
Within a red locket
Of two heart-shaped sides
Lies the face of my blorbo -
It's where he resides.
.
He's well-kept and safe here,
Tended to like a rose,
As I clutch my chest fondly
And my love for him grows.
.
No horror you'll find here,
No tragedies, my friend,
Just a place where he's happy,
Because the world will not end.
.
In here, he is free,
To be himself and to play,
To adventure and explore this world,
With no death flags in the way.
.
I ask for nothing in return
From this dear, dear one to me,
Since the only thing I care to know
Is that my blorbo holds the key.
.
I've found a muse, and it's found me,
And I thank him all the while,
Since I create what I want to see,
And that's my blorbo's smile.
.
I'll carry on for days, I fear
If you ever ask me why.
For him, I'd kill, and him I'd die.
My dearest, beloved,
My blorbo and I.
-
(4.10.22)

Spoken: See, Horsey d'Ville was once a normal horse, roaming through the fields of a planet. So it was he found himself in the path of the Mechanisms some twenty years ago. It was a brutal chase to catch him because he was a damn fast horse. But I, Jonny d'Ville, was determined to get this specific horse.

Victory I would confirm
Offering mechanisation

Forever tumbling sans death

I proposed a solution. Immortality and adoption for Horsey, free from those chasing him. Schematics were drawn up, adoption papers were signed and to complete this historic occasion a mechanism was built to fit Horsey d'Ville, to honor his great intellect that wasn't actually so great, considering he didn't recognise me as the thing chasing him. He inspected it for flaws, he inspected it for traps, he inspected it for viruses. None were found. The surgery was scheduled and joy was unconfined.

body:
I don't know why I'm sharing this, but by far my favorite app on my phone is a korean game called "rainy attic room".
It's about a little guy (or girl, i don't think they ever specify gender) who's depressed and can't leave their room. You're their friend and you can talk to them and take care of them, and slowly their mental health gets better.  
It's not an action game, and the game never pressures you to progress quickly. You're just spending time with your friend who's not feeling so hot, and doing it at your own pace.
It's really cute, and it definitely has helped me a lot with my mental health, because it feels like seeing yourself from an outside perspective. 
Anyway, whenever I see someone in here mention "blorbo from their phone" I think of that game, because you truly start to feel connected to the little character.
(this is NOT sponsored btw)

body:
The sound of galloping breaks through the silence of the forest. Behind them, the enemy amasses. Wielding longswords and torches quick to burn.
There is a man on a horse.
And there is a chasm.
Like a claw driven through rock. The burden of earth’s greatest roars. The rift between one cliff and its lover. It sits there, waiting. Molten tears lying in its stomach, turning the sky above to a wavering suggestion.
There is a man on his horse.
Charging through the trees, the cliff comes into view. Unbeknownst to them, the cliff hungers.
The enemy is getting closer. 
With the closing of eyes and the quiet hush of reassurance, he urges them onwards. They leap.
…
There is a loving man and his cherished companion. Between the two of them, there is one difference.
The man makes it.
The horse does not.
And the rift is full.
----------------------------------------------------

body:
I am almost certain somebody’s made this note before, but. Man. The way memes on most platforms nowadays have a shelf-life so short that by the time you’re done making one, it’s out of style… compared with how ones on Old Internet could go a couple years and still be OK. 
But Tumblr? Tumblr has always been the same. It’s kind of like a reminder of the ways of old. You introduce a meme to these people? It is NEVER going away. In 2022, Spiders Georg lives in harmony with Blorbo From My Shows; Ebony Dark’ness Dementia Raven Way follows the little German boy into the cave of Bluntsmoken; Sans Undertale thrashes Plinkos Plonko, the Plinko Horse. Maybe it’s that we’re 
not like other sites
 (true), or that we’re less susceptible to cringe culture, but there’s something about the lifespan of our memes that warms my heart.

body:
It is a dark and stormy night, and you are alone in your apartment. You got yourself a ouija board the other day and decide to play with it, simply to pass the time. You sit on the floor and surround yourself with candles for ambience.
You speak to the board, hands upon the planchette, bidding the spirits forth. The old building creaks in the wind, rain pattering against the glass of your window. You speak again, louder this time. The lights flicker and dim, then the power goes out, leaving you in the dark but for the candlelight. You think it's probably just a tree falling on the power lines.
You repeat yourself a third time, asking any spirits present to show themselves. You feel a strange chill come over you. Glancing up at the window, you see it is still firmly shut. Despite this, a sudden gust of wind blows out the candles, and just as suddenly falls still, leaving you sitting in total darkness.
You fumble for your lighter, trying to avoid sticking your hands in the hot wax of the candles. Lightning strikes just outside, briefly illuminating the walls.
You freeze.
Frantically you feel for your lighter and after an eternity finally find it. Striking the flint, you confirm that you weren't imagining it: the walls are dripping with blood.
Your own blood runs cold and you clamber backwards over the ouija board towards the center of the room, putting as much distance between yourself and the walls as possible. All you can hear is the storm outside and your heartbeat pounding in your ears, then suddenly the sound of wood scraping against wood.
The dim, flickering light of your lighter doesn't illuminate far, but you can clearly see the planchette moving by itself before you. You stare in horror as it begins to spell out the spirit's demonic message. 
E...
E...
B...
Y...
D...
E...
E...
B...
Y...
You scream, and everything goes black.
Do you think if you were a character, Blorbo would say you were from *their* shows?

I think it’s really interesting that they’ve described Obi-Wan as feeling faithless in the EW spread. I don’t think (mostly because we know his trajectory) that this means he’s lost faith. I think they’re going to show him have a crisis of faith and that crisis then making him a stronger Jedi.
The spiritual people I’ve met that are constantly growing and improving often describe having moments of doubt and faithlessness even without facing something truly horrific. Obi-Wan has gone through a genocide and a war, losing his brother and the people he loved most in the process. I think it’d be strange if his faith wasn’t shaken by these atrocities, if his trust wasn’t broken by the actions of people he called friends. 
But I also know that hope and steadfastness are integral parts of his character. I think he’s going to find these things again throughout the course of the show, coming to terms with his “failure.” And, more so, I think he’s going to find his faith so strongly that Vader’s words aren’t going to be a throw away line anymore. I think Obi-Wan Kenobi is going to grow to believe that Anakin Skywalker still has light in him and Obi-Wan’s going to fight for that light because he is a Jedi and that’s what they do.
